<ARCH_SCAN_V3>
@ID: IAM_LIFECYCLE_REVOCATION_AUDIT
@GOAL: VERIFY_SESSION_TERMINATION_AND_PERMISSION_PROPAGATION_SPEED
@PARENT_CONTEXT: identity_model.protocol, authentication_strategy.protocol

<GLOBAL_VARS>
# Механизмы отзыва (Revocation)
REVOKE_MARKERS: "(revoke|invalidate|logout|blacklist|denyList|banUser)"
TOKEN_STORE: "(redis\.del|cache\.setEx|db\.sessions\.delete)"

# События жизненного цикла
LIFECYCLE_EVENTS: "(onPasswordChange|onRoleUpdate|onAccountLock|onSecurityBreach)"
</GLOBAL_VARS>

<CONTEXT_MAP>
[REVOKER]      <- {match: {{REVOKE_MARKERS}}, scope: "FUNCTION"}
[SESSIONS_DB]  <- {match: {{TOKEN_STORE}}, layer: [PERSIST]}
[EVENT_BUS]    <- {match: {{MESSAGE_BUS}}, context: "security_event"}
</CONTEXT_MAP>

<ASSERTIONS>
# Логические инварианты жизненного цикла
! (PASSWORD_CHANGE) & !(REVOKE_ALL_SESSIONS) : "CRITICAL: Changing password does not invalidate existing active sessions. High risk of persistent hijacker access."
! (JWT_AUTH) & !([SESSIONS_DB] | SHORT_TTL) : "HIGH: Stateless JWTs cannot be revoked before expiration. Use a Blacklist or very short TTL."
? (ROLE_UPDATE) -> !IMMEDIATE_EFFECT : "MEDIUM: Role changes only take effect after next login (Inconsistent state risk)."
! (LOGOUT_FUNC) -> !([SESSIONS_DB].delete) : "HIGH: Logout only clears client-side state, leaving the server-side session/token valid."
</ASSERTIONS>

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. LOGOUT_INTEGRITY_CHECK:
   - Identify the `logout` implementation.
   - Verify if it actively invalidates the token/session in [SESSIONS_DB] or just deletes a cookie.
2. SECURITY_EVENT_PROPAGATION:
   - Trace what happens during {{LIFECYCLE_EVENTS}}.
   - Ensure that a 'Password Reset' triggers a global [REVOKER] call for ALL active tokens of that user.
3. BLACKLIST_MECHANISM_AUDIT:
   - If using JWT, identify the storage for revoked tokens (e.g., Redis).
   - Check if the [API_LEVEL] guard checks this list on EVERY request.
4. ACCOUNT_LOCKOUT_LOGIC:
   - Verify if `user.isActive = false` or `user.isLocked` is respected by the [AUTH_STRATEGY].
   - Ensure a locked user cannot use an already issued (but not expired) token.
5. STALE_SESSION_CLEANUP:
   - Check for background jobs that prune expired sessions/tokens from [SESSIONS_DB] to prevent resource exhaustion.
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
GENERATE_REVOCATION_REPORT:
  - TRIGGER_EVENT | REVOCATION_METHOD | PROPAGATION_SPEED (Sync/Async) | SECURITY_GAP
VISUALIZE: "Flowchart: Password_Change -> Event_Bus -> All_Sessions_Terminated."
FILTER: RISK >= MEDIUM
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</ARCH_SCAN_V3>